      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis, which directly maps to the relative hemolysis index used as the COU acceptance criterion. Pressure head is a secondary QoI confirming hydraulic performance fidelity. Both QoIs are directly relevant to the worst-case hemolysis identification objective."
